The paper focuses on the task of traffic scene perception, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a learning-based detection framework, which involves the use of dense feature extractors and detectors for three important classes of objects. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with the tracking of objects in motion, which is a subfield of robotics, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper deals with the detection of objects in noisy and deformed images, which is a subfield of computer security, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
